    {
      "id": "PopularPost282919",
      "post_content": "I was just browsing TV Tropes when i realized i never actually read this card's flavor text, since it was used as the introductionary quote for the *Weapon of Choice* trope \"Simple Staff\".  \nNow we need a [Simple Staff](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Simple Staff) equipment that's as awesome as the trope suggests it ought to be! :D  \nSince this card is a kor and these folks just coincidentally happen to be great martial artists (or at least the newer ones are particularly good with equipment), i could imagine this equipment providing a bonus if it's equipped to a kor.  \n(For example this card's trigger, or a further bonus like a +1/+1 boost, first strike or similar stuff.)  \n  \nWell, about the trigger: in general it's mostly a bad version of *Vigilance*, but i could imagine some borderline uses where it's preferable (e.g. through cards triggering on permanents tapping/untapping).",
      "posted_by": "Mode",
      "html": "<div class=\"post evenItem\" id=\"PopularPost282919\" style=\"background-color: rgba(255,255,255,0.08);\">\n<span class=\"postContent\" id=\"ctl00_ctl00_ctl00_MainContent_SubContent_SubContent_popularPosts_postsRepeater_ctl04_post\">I was just browsing TV Tropes when i realized i never actually read this card's flavor text, since it was used as the introductionary quote for the <i>Weapon of Choice</i> trope \"Simple Staff\".<br/>Now we need a <a class=\"autoCard\" data:cardname=\"Simple Staff\" href=\"/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Simple Staff\">Simple Staff</a> equipment that's as awesome as the trope suggests it ought to be! :D<br/>Since this card is a kor and these folks just coincidentally happen to be great martial artists (or at least the newer ones are particularly good with equipment), i could imagine this equipment providing a bonus if it's equipped to a kor.<br/>(For example this card's trigger, or a further bonus like a +1/+1 boost, first strike or similar stuff.)<br/><br/>Well, about the trigger: in general it's mostly a bad version of <i>Vigilance</i>, but i could imagine some borderline uses where it's preferable (e.g. through cards triggering on permanents tapping/untapping).</span>\n<div class=\"postDetails\" id=\"ctl00_ctl00_ctl00_MainContent_SubContent_SubContent_popularPosts_postsRepeater_ctl04_postDetails\" style=\"padding-top: 5px;\">\n<div class=\"reportAbuse\">\n<a href=\"../../Classes/Controls/#\" id=\"ctl00_ctl00_ctl00_MainContent_SubContent_SubContent_popularPosts_postsRepeater_ctl04_reportAbuseLink\" onclick=\"HandleReportPost(this, '282919'); return false;\">\r\n                                    Report Abuse</a>\u00a0\u00a0\r\n                                    \r\n                            </div>\n<div class=\"postedBy\">\r\n                                Posted By: \r\n                                <span id=\"PostedBy416\">Mode</span>\r\n                                (11/25/2012 10:29:40 AM)\r\n                 